  "title": "Class 3 VAN/BUS Driver (Tourism ) -URGENT",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Job Description</strong></h3><p>We are looking for a <strong>reliable and responsible Class 3 Driver with BDVL</strong> to join our tourism transport operations. This role involves shuttle-based and point-to-point services for tourists across Singapore.</p><p>The ideal candidate must be calm under pressure, punctual, and able to handle a fast-paced working environment.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Perform <strong>shuttle-based and point-to-point transfers</strong></p></li><li><p>Handle <strong>SIC (Seat-In-Coach)</strong> services</p></li><li><p>Conduct <strong>arrival & departure airport transfers</strong></p></li><li><p>Ensure safe, smooth, and timely transportation of passengers</p></li><li><p>Maintain professionalism while handling guests</p></li><li><p>Follow company schedules and operational instructions strictly</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Work Schedule</strong></h3><ul><li><p><strong>6 days per week</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Up to 12 hours per day</strong></p></li><li><p>Tourism operations may involve <strong>peak hours, rush periods, and tight schedules</strong></p></li><li><p>Some days may be <strong>physically tiring with limited rest</strong>, especially during high-demand periods</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Valid <strong>Class 3 Driving Licence</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>BDVL (Bus Driver Vocational Licence) – Mandatory</strong></p></li><li><p>Prior experience in <strong>tourism or shuttle operations</strong> preferred</p></li><li><p>Able to <strong>handle rush and panic situations calmly</strong></p></li><li><p>Physically fit and mentally resilient</p></li><li><p>Responsible, punctual, and customer-focused</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Salary & Benefits</strong></h3><ul><li><p><strong>Monthly fixed salary: SGD 3,600 – 3,700</strong><br /><em>(Inclusive of CPF contributions)</em></p></li><li><p>Stable, long-term <strong>tourism sector job</strong></p></li><li><p>Opportunity to work with a growing transport & travel group</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Additional Information</strong></h3><p>This is a <strong>tourism operations role</strong>, and candidates must be prepared for:</p><ul><li><p>Irregular peak timings</p></li><li><p>Fast-paced work environment</p></li><li><p>High passenger volume on certain days</p></li></ul><p>Applicants who understand the nature of tourism transport and are committed to delivering reliable service are encouraged to apply.</p>",
